A magnitude-5.8 earthquake hit Maerkang City in southwest China's Sichuan Province at 12:03 a.m. Friday, according to the China Earthquake Networks Center (CENC). Several aftershocks ensued, the strongest being magnitude 6.0 at a depth of 13 kilometers. Disaster relief work is underway as firefighters were deployed to the earthquake zone overnight. The situation is being further examined. Currently, there is no reported casualties. China's Ministry of Emergency Management has launched a level-4 emergency response.